Wash and dry all produce (except green beans). Peel and grate or mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (zest 1 lime; quarter both for 4 servings). Chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves and stems). Halve and peel @shallot{1}; mince one half (mince both halves for 4). Mince half the @garlic{2%clove} (mince all the garlic for 4).

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), @brown sugar{1%tablespoon}, and 1/2 tsp @salt{} (1 tsp for 4). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @shredded coconut{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring constantly, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}. Turn off heat and wipe out pan.

Pierce green bean bag with a fork; place bag on a plate. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. (TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam @green beans{6%ounce} in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.) Transfer to a #medium bowl{} and toss with @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub all over with @turmeric{1%teaspoon}. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in pan used for coconut over medium-high heat. Add tilapia; cook until firm and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan. Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add ginger, shallot, and garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Stir in 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and juice from half the lime. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Add @butter{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) to pan with sauce. Stir in half the cilantro and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fluff rice; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}, coconut, and lime zest. Divide rice, green beans, and tilapia between plates. Spoon sauce over tilapia. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.